    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing CTRL-C (instead of ESC) to exit visual block insert mode only inserts the text that was just entered, instead of inserting it in front of the entire selection. Also interestingly, using '.' to repeat the action does the insert correctly.\n\nI tried to create a test for this behaviour, but ran into some issues. Whenever I used `<C-c>` in a `feed()` call, the test just failed with empty output.\n\nWhen using `nvim_replace_termcodes` and `nvim_feedkeys` to send a `<C-c>`, the test **passes**, which is very strange. The only way I found to reproduce what actually happens is just by not exiting visual block at all before the test ends.\n\nCommit with attempted test:\nhttps://github.com/dwgrth/neovim/commit/794a8f161b8810182ce4536d6936172f222f8e00\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n`iabc<CR>abc<CR>abc<C-c>gg^<C-v>GIxyz<C-c>`\n\n--- Actual output:\nxyzabc\nabc\nabc\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n--- Expected output:\nxyzabc\nxyzabc\nxyzabc\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1.0016-1ubuntu7.3\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
